# DataFlow WebUI Frontend (Vue 3 + Vite)

> **⚠ CHANGE POLICY**: Before creating any new page, route, or nav item, check `webui-change-policy.mdc`. Only operator rendering fixes and missing param editors are allowed. New dashboard pages, analytics views, and feature-level UI are prohibited unless the user explicitly overrides.

## Tech Stack

- **Vue 3** + **Vite**
- **Vue Router** (hash history: `createWebHashHistory`)
- **Pinia** (setup-store style)
- **Vue Flow** (`@vue-flow/core`) for pipeline DAG editor
- **VueFluent3** (`@creatorsn/vfluent3`) for UI components
- **Axios** for API calls (auto-generated from OpenAPI)

## Two Component Styles (both are used)

| Area | Style |
|---|---|
| `mainFlow/nodes/`, new components | `<script setup>` + `defineProps` / `defineEmits` |
| `mainFlow/pipeline/`, panels, views | Options API: `export default { props, data, computed, methods }` |

**Do NOT convert existing components between styles.** Match the style of the file you're editing.

## Router — Adding a New Manage Page

1. Add route in `frontend/src/router/Manage/index.js`:
```javascript
{
    path: 'my-page',
    component: () => AsyncLoad(() => import('@/views/manage/myPage/index.vue')),
    meta: { title: 'Dataflow-MyPage' }
}
```

2. Add nav item in `frontend/src/views/manage/index.vue` (`navList` array):
```javascript
{
    key: 4,
    name: () => this.local('My Page'),
    icon: 'ViewDashboard',
    route: '/m/my-page'
}
```

3. Create `frontend/src/views/manage/myPage/index.vue`

**Note:** Lazy loading uses `AsyncLoad` wrapper (not raw `import()`), defined in `router/tools.js`.

## Vue Flow Pipeline Editor

The pipeline canvas is `components/manage/mainFlow/index.vue`. Key architecture:

### Node Types (registered via slots)

```html
<VueFlow v-model:nodes="thisNodes" v-model:edges="thisEdges">
    <template #node-base-node="nodeProps">
        <baseNode v-bind="nodeProps" />
    </template>
    <template #node-operator-node="nodeProps">
        <operatorNode v-bind="nodeProps" @update-node-data="updateNodeData" />
    </template>
    <template #node-database-node="nodeProps">
        <databaseNode v-bind="nodeProps" />
    </template>
</VueFlow>
```

### Adding Nodes Programmatically

```javascript
import { useVueFlow } from '@vue-flow/core'

const flow = useVueFlow(flowId)
flow.addNodes({
    id: $Guid(),
    type: 'operator-node',      // must match a #node-xxx slot
    position: { x: 100, y: 200 },
    data: {
        flowId: props.id,
        label: 'MyOperator',
        ...operatorData
    }
})
```

### Node Component Pattern (`<script setup>`)

```javascript
import { computed } from 'vue'
import { Position, Handle } from '@vue-flow/core'

const props = defineProps({
    id: { type: String, required: true },
    position: { type: Object, required: true },
    selected: { type: Boolean, default: false },
    data: { type: Object, default: () => ({}) }
})

const emits = defineEmits(['delete-node', 'update-node-data'])
```

## Pinia Stores

**Setup-store style** (this project's convention):

```javascript
import { defineStore } from 'pinia'
import { ref, computed, getCurrentInstance } from 'vue'

export const useMyStore = defineStore('useMyStore', () => {
    const instance = getCurrentInstance()
    const proxy = instance.proxy   // access $api, $barWarning, etc.

    const items = ref([])
    const loading = ref(false)

    const getItems = async () => {
        const res = await proxy.$api.myResource.list_items()
        if (res.code === 200) {
            items.value = res.data
        }
    }

    return { items, loading, getItems }
})
```

**In Options API components**, use `mapState` / `mapActions`:
```javascript
import { mapState, mapActions } from 'pinia'
import { useDataflow } from '@/stores/dataflow'

computed: {
    ...mapState(useDataflow, ['pipelines', 'operators'])
},
methods: {
    ...mapActions(useDataflow, ['getPipelines', 'getOperators'])
}
```

## API Calls

**Global access**: `this.$api` (Options API) or `useGlobal().$api` (Composition API)

```javascript
// Options API
this.$api.pipelines.list_pipelines().then(res => {
    if (res.code === 200) { /* res.data */ }
})

// Composition API
import { useGlobal } from '@/hooks/general/useGlobal'
const { $api } = useGlobal()
const res = await $api.datasets.list_datasets()
```

**Response shape**: `{ success, code, message, data, meta }`. Check `res.code === 200` for success.

**API client** is auto-generated in `frontend/src/axios/api.js` from OpenAPI. Each domain is an exported class with static async methods. To add a new endpoint call, add a static method following the existing pattern.

## VueFluent3 UI Components

**Always pass `:theme="theme"`** to VueFluent components. Common components:

| Component | Usage |
|---|---|
| `<fv-button>` | Buttons (`:borderRadius="8"`, `:isBoxShadow="true"`) |
| `<fv-text-box>` | Text input |
| `<fv-combobox>` | Dropdown select |
| `<fv-pivot>` | Tab navigation |
| `<fv-expander>` | Collapsible sections |
| `<fv-toggle-switch>` | Boolean toggle |
| `<fv-progress-ring>` | Loading spinner |
| `<fv-drop-down>` | Dropdown menu |
| `<fv-details-list>` | Data table |
| `<fv-navigation-view>` | Side navigation (used in manage layout) |
| `<fv-command-bar>` | Toolbar |

**Icons**: Segoe MDL2 classes — `<i class="ms-Icon ms-Icon--Add"></i>`

## Global Utilities

```javascript
// Composition API — useGlobal()
import { useGlobal } from '@/hooks/general/useGlobal'
const { $api, $router, $Guid, $infoBox, $barWarning } = useGlobal()

// Options API — this.$xxx
this.$api        // API client
this.$router     // Vue Router
this.$Guid()     // Generate UUID
this.$infoBox    // Info dialog
this.$barWarning // Warning toast
```

## i18n

```javascript
// In Options API (via mapActions)
import { mapActions } from 'pinia'
import { useAppConfig } from '@/stores/appConfig'

methods: {
    ...mapActions(useAppConfig, ['local']),
    // Usage in template: {{ local('Pipeline') }}
}

// In Composition API
const appConfig = useAppConfig()
appConfig.local('Pipeline')
```

